{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Classes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/LiveText"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/delegate"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/config(sliceHeight:numSlicesVisible:duration:autoScroll:)","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/sendAction(action:)","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/sendImage(image:slicePosition:scrollFirst:)"]},{"title":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayo